by /DC=ch/DC=cern/OU=Organic Units/OU=Users/CN=destefan/CN=665120/CN=John Steven De Stefano Jr</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='30079#1464891489'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2016-06-02T18:18:09+00:00">Jun 2, 2016 06:18 PM UTC</time> by <b>Sarah Schmiechen</b><a class="anchor" name="1464891489">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>HI John,

ISSUE and PROJ are how Footprints keeps track of the tickets. This tickets that we are using now is in Footprints behind the scenes, and the cert notification emails are actually generated by updates to Footprints tickets, which then sends out emails. So the project and issue parts have to stay in there. So the subject part might actually be trickier to change, as that’s generic to all our tickets, not just the cert ones. But we can change the body however we like.  (Just a bit of background info there).

I’ll get something in ITB and let you know when you can test.

Thanks!
Sarah</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='30079#1464889479'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2016-06-02T17:44:39+00:00">Jun 2, 2016 05:44 PM UTC</time><a class="anchor" name="1464889479">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Hi Sarah,

