<a href='https&#58;//ticket.grid.iu.edu/goc/30064' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//ticket.grid.iu.edu/goc/30064</a>
The subject of of the notification email for this ticket reads&#58; &#34;Ticket Creation Notification ISSUE=30064 PROJ=71&#34;
One line of the ticket notification body reads&#58;
&#34;Your issue &#34;Host Certificate Request by John S. De Stefano Jr.(OIM user)&#34; has been entered into our system as ticket number 30064, and will be given full attention.&#34;
The rest of the ticket notification is boilerplate and makes no mention of the content of the ticket, let alone the host for which the ticket was created.
The resolution ticket notification is quite similar in this way&#58; It contains boilerplate and the line, &#34;John S. De Stefano Jr. has issued certificate. Resolving this ticket.&#34;
It would be quite useful if you could please include the host name of hosts for which certificate request tickets are generated in the ticket notifications themselves, at least within the body of the notification, but perhaps also in the notification subject, which could also include the title of the ticket.

